begin_memory_text: Some introductions and where we from, and some thoughts about the covid-19 situation. He was from Alaska, and I asked him a few questions about what it was like living there.
middle_memory_text: Conversation continued to revolve around covid and where were from for the most part. He lived in San Francisco for a bit, so that was a talking point. We talked about how each respective state handled the covid situation
end_memory_text: Some discussion about our hobbies, some of this centered around piano for a while since we both played it. Beyond that we largely talked about living in a more secluded area like Alaska versus a more urban one.
rest_of_day_open: I finished some exams the other week, so I have a lot more free time moving forward. Towards the end of the week though I will need to start worrying about more assignments again. At this point I have just accepted my endless cycle of stressing out and deflating every other week.
critical_positive: I think our personalities were on a more similar wavelength compared to my previous encounters. It was, at least on the surface, a lot more of a relaxed conversation. There was more humor involved too, which is more of my style of conversation. More laughter over all made it easier to work through it.
critical_negative: I think I came off a little strong/annoying. I kept asking about what it was like living in a relatively desolate area of the country. I was just grasping for conversation topics but I think I ended up coming off as a city person who can't appreciate what it's like living in a more rural environment.

begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves and talked about where we lived and what we did for a living. We talked about the pandemic a little bit also.
middle_memory_text: We mostly talked about the pandemic and the impacts it has had on our lives. He talked about being home in California because his university was doing entirely online classes.
end_memory_text: We talked about what we did for fun. We both play piano and we talked about how we find and learn new music. We also talked about places we have traveled.
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week will be busy but good. I have a fair amount of stuff that I need to get done. The end of the week I am going on a trip which I am excited about. That part of the week will be excellent. I cant wait to get to some warm weather!
critical_positive: Everything worked just fine. We found stuff to talk about and the technology portion of things went well. We mostly talked about how the pandemic was impacting our lives and how things have changed for each of us. We also both play the piano which we talked about for a while.
critical_negative: We seem pretty far apart in age and experience so we didnt have a ton to talk about. He hasnt traveled very much and plays a lot of video games. I love to travel and have been all over the world and basically never play video games. That made it a little challenging to find things to talk about.
